                <note rend="inline" type="source">833.24/7–1544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-15">July 15,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1140. Our Embassy in Montevideo reports that a serious situation in <hi
                        rend="italic">frigoríficos</hi> may soon result from action of Argentine
                    Government in denying all export permits for shipment of salt to Uruguay. Please
                    report immediately whether there is a shortage of salt in Argentina or whether
                    we should interpret the action of the Argentine Government as an economic
                    sanction against Uruguay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
